First Lady Michelle Obama expresses her gratitude to Director Kemper and the Institute of Museum and Library Services for their commitment to making museums and libraries accessible to all. She shares her personal experience of falling in love with learning through books and emphasizes the importance of libraries and museums in providing a world of possibilities for children. She highlights how museums and libraries are living parts of communities, weaving together the stories of the nation and safeguarding freedom to learn and explore without fear of censorship. Mrs. Obama mentions the temporary exhibit of young adult and children's books installed in the White House library, with the hope of making them a permanent part of the living museum. She acknowledges the significant impact of libraries and museums in changing lives, from inspiring careers in science to providing support for job searches and offering tools for personal growth. Mrs. Obama concludes by commending the awardees for their dedication and inviting them to join her on stage for their citations.